  "doc_id": "42928",
  "text": "Thus, although better data are needed to determine the sizes of the CNO-free zones, the very existence of such zones at the centres of pre-stellar cores implies that the relative abundances of H + 3 , H 2 D + and D 2 H + are sensitive to the grain size [CITATION_1] ) and the o/p H 2 ratio (Flower et al. 2006) . Normally, these parameters are very hard to constrain by observations because of other competing effects. The centres of pre-stellar cores thus form a unique laboratory to study basic physical parameters of interstellar gas.",
